### Your Task

_You are hired by a travel agency to help them with the digitalization of their business. Here they need you to finish the implementation of this user interface, which allows them to keep track of all of the destinations they offer holidays to._

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**Write the missing JavaScript function**  **addDestination** **()** to make the **[Add Destination]** button work as expected – when clicked **adds** the new destination to the table with destinations and **updates** the destinations per season section at the bottom. The **[Add]** button should:

-
 **Append** the **text** received from the **input boxes** and the **text** of the **selected season** from the **dropdown** as a **new**** row at the end **of the** table&#39;s body **. The** destination **name should bein the following format** :**

&quot;{city}, {country}&quot;

- **Update** the **number of destinations per season** in the **&quot;**** summaryBox ****&quot;** section.
- **Clear** the **input boxes** after the **destination&#39;s information** is **submitted**.
- **Do nothing** if **either** of **text boxes** is **empty**.

### Submission

Submit only your **addDestination** function.
